<body>
  <header>
    <h1>Alex Ballagh — Platform for Ward 8</h1>
  </header>

  <section>
    <h2>Aging Infrastructure & Safer Streets</h2>
    <p>Our roads, sidewalks, and community spaces must be safe and accessible for everyone — from kids to seniors. I will push for:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Complete-streets upgrades on key corridors like Upper James and Rymal Road with sidewalks, bike lanes, and curb accessibility.</li>
      <li>Neighbourhood sidewalk repairs and traffic calming to protect pedestrians and cyclists.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Road Safety & Traffic Calming</h2>
    <p>Speeding and heavy truck traffic threaten our residential streets. My priorities include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Installing additional speed humps in Rolston and Bonnington.</li>
      <li>Improving intersections such as Claremont Access for safer vehicle and pedestrian flow.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Community Safety & Partnerships</h2>
    <p>Working collaboratively with police and community groups to reduce crime and increase safety, I will advocate for:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>More foot patrols and community policing in hotspot areas.</li>
      <li>Targeted intervention and youth programs to address root causes of crime.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Affordable Housing & Tenant Protections</h2>
    <p>Housing should be attainable and safe for all residents. I will champion:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Gentle density policies, supporting duplexes and townhomes to increase affordable supply.</li>
      <li>A vacant property tax to discourage speculation and empty homes.</li>
      <li>A maximum heat bylaw to guarantee tenants safe, livable temperatures year-round.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Union Rights & Workers’ Protections</h2>
    <p>I support strong unions and workers by:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Fighting for fair wages, workplace safety, and the right to organize.</li>
      <li>Backing local efforts to strengthen labour protections and job security.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Transit & LRT Readiness</h2>
    <p>To get more people out of their cars, I will:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Push for improved bus routes and expanded weekend service.</li>
      <li>Lead public education campaigns about the LRT to ensure smooth transit connections.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Parks, Trails & Recreation</h2>
    <p>Everyone deserves access to safe, welcoming green spaces. I’ll work to:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Build equitable splash pads and connect trails along the escarpment.</li>
      <li>Ensure accessibility for families and seniors in all new park projects.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Climate Action & Sustainability</h2>
    <p>Ward 8 must be a leader in climate resilience. I will fight for:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Expanded tree planting and biodiversity initiatives.</li>
      <li>Electrification of city fleets and green development policies.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Healthcare & Education Supports</h2>
    <p>Stronger healthcare and educational resources are essential. I will advocate for:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Improved access to local health services, including mental health supports.</li>
      <li>Community education programs for youth and seniors.</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

